 width="100" height="100" alt="olive oil" title="olive oil" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/olive-oil">Olive oil</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">ol-iv oyl</span><p>Probably the most widely-used oil in cooking, olive oil is pressed from fresh olives. It's…</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="500g boneless, skinless chicken thigh">500g boneless, skinless chicken thigh</li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="flour, for dusting"><a href="/glossary/flour" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--2 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">flour</a>, for dusting<span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--2"><article id="node-257912" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/flour"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/flour_0.jpg?itok=f_OiRpqB" width="100" height="100" alt="Flour" title="Flour is a powdery ingredient usually made from grinding wheat, maize, rye, barley or rice" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/flour">Flour</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">fl-ow-er</span><p>Flour is a powdery ingredient usually made from grinding wheat, maize, rye, barley or rice. As…</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="50g cubetti di pancetta">50g cubetti di <a href="/glossary/pancetta" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--3 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">pancetta</a><span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--3"><article id="node-253866" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/pancetta"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/pancetta-resizedd.jpg?itok=z-PY2UlX" width="100" height="100" alt="Pancetta" title="Pancetta" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/pancetta">Pancetta</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">pan-chet-ah</span><p>Pancetta is Italian cured pork belly - the equivalent of streaky bacon. It has a deep, strong,…</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="300g small button mushroom">300g small button mushroom</li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="2 large shallots, chopped">2 large <a href="/glossary/shallot" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--4 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">shallots</a>, chopped<span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--4"><article id="node-253846" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/shallot"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/shallot.jpg?itok=6KWhGf6M" width="100" height="100" alt="Shallot" title="Related to the onion, shallots grow in clusters at the leaf base" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/shallot">Shallot</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">shal-lot</span><p>Related to the onion (as opposed to being a younger version of it), shallots grow in clusters at…</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="250ml chicken stock">250ml chicken stock</li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="1 tbsp white wine vinegar">1 tbsp white wine vinegar</li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="50g frozen pea">50g frozen pea</li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="small handful parsley, finely chopped">small handful <a href="/glossary/parsley" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--5 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">parsley</a>, finely chopped<span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--5"><article id="node-259636" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/parsley"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/parsley.jpg?itok=ZJpglKu3" width="100" height="100" alt="Parsley" title="The traditional British choice is curly parsley, but flat leaved (Continental) parsley is also widely available" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/parsley">Parsley</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">par-slee</span><p>One of the most ubiquitous herbs in British cookery, parsley is also popular in European and…</p> </article></span></li></ul></div></div> </section> <section id="recipe-method" class="responsive-tabs__pane"><h2 class="responsive-tabs__pane-title">Method</h2><div class="method"><ol class="method__list"><li class="method__item" itemprop="recipeInstructions"><p>Heat 1 tbsp oil in a frying pan. Season and dust the chicken with flour, brown on all sides. Remove. Fry the pancetta and mushrooms until softened, then remove.</p></li><li class="method__item" itemprop="recipeInstructions"><p>Add the final tbsp oil and cook shallots for 5 mins. Add the stock and vinegar, bubble for 1-2 mins. Return the chicken, pancetta and mushrooms and cook for 15 mins. Add the peas and parsley and cook for 2 mins more, then serve.</p></li></ol></div> <footer class="recipe-info"><div class="recipe-info__publication">Recipe from Good Food magazine, <a href="/search/recipes/date/1349046000" class="text-style-alt">October 2012</a></div> <a class="recipe-info__magazine-ad" href=" https://www.buysubscriptions.com/print/bbc-good-food-magazine-subscription?promo=GFBS718&style=Brand&utm_medium=brandsite&utm_source=bbcgoodfood.com&utm_campaign=recipe_GFBS718_Brand&utm_content=recipe-banner" rel="external" onclick="Drupal.GFAnalytics.trackEvent(['Magazines', 'subscribe', 'Recipe' ])"> <img src="https://www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/magazine/gf_aug18_337x109.jpg" alt="BBC GoodFood Magazine" /> </a> </footer> </section></div></div> <section id="block-bbcgf-search-views-bbcgf-cc-rel-recipes" class="section-box section-box--you-may-also-like"> <header class="section-box__header"><h2 class="section-box__title">You may also like</h2> </header><div class="section-box__content"><div class="carousel"><div class="flexslider type-1" data-type="1"><ul class="slides"><li class=""><article id="node-97457" class="node node-recipe node-carousel-slide-narrow clearfix"><div class="vertical-push-item__image"> <img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/carousel_small/public/recipe_images/recipe-image-legacy-id--1167480_11.jpg?itok=YE-UyomZ" width="324" height="294" alt="Chicken, butter bean &amp; pepper stew" title="Chicken, butter bean &amp; pepper stew" /></div><h3 class="vertical-push-item__title"> <a href="/recipes/2778662/chicken-butter-bean-and-pepper-stew"> Chicken, butter bean &amp; pepper stew </a></h3><div class="push-item__ratings"><div class="clearfix fivestar-average-stars fivestar-average-text"><div class="fivestar-static-form-item"><div class="form-item form-type-item"><div class="field-main"><div class="fivestar-bbcgoodfood"><div class="clearfix fivestar-widget-static fivestar-widget-stati